---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const siblingServices = [
  { name: "Root Canal Treatment", href: "/services/endodontics/root-canal" },
  { name: "Traumatic Dental Injuries", href: "/services/endodontics/traumatic-injuries" },
  { name: "Cracked Tooth", href: "/services/endodontics/cracked-tooth", current: true },
  { name: "Internal Tooth Bleaching", href: "/services/endodontics/internal-bleaching" },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cracked Tooth | Endodontic Care | Able Family Dental Lethbridge"
  description="Cracked tooth treatment at Able Family Dental in Lethbridge. Understanding cracked tooth syndrome, its causes, symptoms, and management options."
>

  <!-- ============================================================
       HERO
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] relative overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Right-side image panel, desktop only -->
    <div class="hidden lg:block absolute right-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-[42%] pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true">
      <img
        src="/images/bugherd/ChatGPT_Image_Jun_2_2026_12_17_55_PM.png"
        alt=""
        width="800"
        height="600"
        loading="eager"
        decoding="async"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 w-2/5" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--color-brand-primary), transparent);"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container-wide relative py-16 lg:py-24 lg:max-w-[64%]">
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-white mb-5" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="text-white hover:text-white/80 transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <a href="/services/" class="text-white/80 hover:text-white transition-colors">Services</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <a href="/services/endodontics/" class="text-white/80 hover:text-white transition-colors">Endodontic Services</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <span class="text-white">Cracked Tooth</span>
      </nav>
      <p class="eyebrow text-white">Endodontic Care</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-5xl)] leading-tight text-white max-w-2xl">
        Cracked Tooth
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
        Cracked tooth syndrome involves pain or discomfort related to a crack in a tooth, often intermittent and sometimes difficult to pinpoint. Understanding the type and extent of the crack guides the appropriate treatment.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       MAIN CONTENT + SIDEBAR
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="section-y bg-white">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_300px] gap-12">

        <!-- LEFT: Main content -->
        <div class="space-y-10">

          <!-- What is cracked tooth syndrome -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              What is cracked tooth syndrome?
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Cracked tooth syndrome refers to pain or sensitivity associated with a crack in a tooth, particularly pain that occurs when biting or chewing, or a sharp momentary pain when releasing bite pressure. The discomfort is often intermittent, and patients may find it difficult to identify which tooth is causing it or under what conditions the pain occurs.
              </p>
              <p>
                Unlike a fracture that splits the tooth visibly, many cracks are incomplete, they extend into the tooth structure but do not result in a broken-off piece. This makes them harder to detect and harder to diagnose definitively.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Image break -->
          <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden max-h-[700px]">
            <img
              src="/images/bugherd/Update.png"
              alt="Cracked tooth treatment at Able Family Dental"
              width="800"
              height="450"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
              class="w-full h-auto"
            />
          </div>


          <!-- Why cracks happen -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              Why cracks develop
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Tooth structure can crack for a number of reasons:
              </p>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-3">
                {[
                  ["Grinding and clenching (bruxism)", "Sustained clenching or grinding places significant repetitive force on the teeth, which can cause cracks over time."],
                  ["Chewing hard objects", "Biting down on hard foods, ice, or non-food items can initiate or extend a crack."],
                  ["Large restorations", "Teeth with large fillings have less intact tooth structure to support the biting load, which can increase the risk of cracking over time."],
                  ["Temperature changes", "Repeated exposure to extreme temperature changes can contribute to crack development in some teeth."],
                  ["Trauma", "A direct blow or impact can crack a tooth even if the tooth does not visibly fracture."],
                ].map(([title, body]) => (
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <svg class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-[var(--color-brand-accent)]" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="5 12 10 17 19 7"/></svg>
                    <div>
                      <span class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)]">{title}</span>
                      <span class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">, {body}</span>
                    </div>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Types of cracks -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              Types of tooth cracks
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              {[
                {
                  name: "Craze lines",
                  detail: "Fine surface cracks confined to the outer enamel. They are very common and do not typically require treatment, they are not associated with pain and do not threaten the structural integrity of the tooth.",
                },
                {
                  name: "Fractured cusp",
                  detail: "A piece of the biting surface breaks away, often around an existing large filling. The fracture usually does not reach the pulp, and the tooth can be restored with a new filling or a crown.",
                },
                {
                  name: "Cracked tooth",
                  detail: "A crack that begins at the biting surface and extends downward toward the root. The crack has not yet split the tooth into separate pieces. Depending on how far it extends, treatment may involve a crown, root canal therapy, or both. The sooner a crack like this is addressed, the more options are available.",
                },
                {
                  name: "Split tooth",
                  detail: "The crack has extended through the tooth, resulting in distinct segments. A split tooth cannot typically be saved intact, partial retention may be possible in some cases, but often extraction is required.",
                },
                {
                  name: "Vertical root fracture",
                  detail: "A fracture that originates in the root and extends upward. These are often asymptomatic for an extended period and may only be detected when the surrounding bone and gum begin to show signs of infection. Extraction is usually required.",
                },
              ].map(item => (
                <div class="border-l-4 border-[var(--color-brand-accent)] pl-5">
                  <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-base text-[var(--color-brand-primary)]">{item.name}</h3>
                  <p class="mt-1.5 text-sm text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">{item.detail}</p>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Symptoms -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              Symptoms
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                The symptoms of a cracked tooth can vary considerably. Common presentations include:
              </p>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-3">
                {[
                  "Sharp pain when biting down, or upon releasing bite pressure",
                  "Sensitivity to temperature, cold or heat, that may linger",
                  "Intermittent discomfort that is difficult to reproduce predictably",
                  "Difficulty identifying which tooth is causing the pain",
                ].map(item => (
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <svg class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-[var(--color-brand-accent)]" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="5 12 10 17 19 7"/></svg>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">{item}</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-3">
                The intermittent nature of symptoms can make cracked tooth syndrome one of the more challenging dental conditions to diagnose.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Diagnosis -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-surface-cool)] rounded-2xl p-7 border border-[var(--color-border-soft)]">
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-2xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] leading-tight">
              How cracks are diagnosed
            </h2>
            <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                There is no single test that reliably detects all cracks. Diagnosis typically involves a combination of approaches:
              </p>
              <ul class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
                {[
                  "A detailed history of when and how the pain occurs",
                  "Bite tests using a bite stick to reproduce and isolate the symptom",
                  "Transillumination, shining a light through the tooth to reveal cracks",
                  "Visual examination, including staining agents that can highlight crack lines",
                  "X-rays, though many cracks are not visible on x-rays",
                ].map(item => (
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                    <svg class="mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[var(--color-brand-accent)]" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="5 12 10 17 19 7"/></svg>
                    <span>{item}</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-3">
                In some cases the crack may not be identifiable until the tooth is examined under magnification or in certain lighting conditions. We will take whatever time is needed to investigate the source of your symptoms carefully.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Treatment -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">
              Treatment
            </h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Treatment depends on the type, location, and extent of the crack:
              </p>
              <ul class="mt-3 space-y-3">
                {[
                  "A crown is often recommended to hold the tooth together and prevent the crack from extending further with biting forces.",
                  "If the crack has reached the pulp, root canal treatment may be needed before the crown is placed.",
                  "A split tooth or vertical root fracture may require extraction if the tooth cannot be maintained.",
                ].map(item => (
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                    <svg class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-[var(--color-brand-accent)]" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="5 12 10 17 19 7"/></svg>
                    <span class="text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">{item}</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
              <p class="mt-3">
                Cracks that extend toward or into the root are generally more difficult to treat, and early detection is associated with a wider range of management options. If you are experiencing intermittent biting pain or sensitivity, it is worth having it assessed sooner rather than later.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Specialty disclaimer -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-surface-alt)] rounded-2xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border-soft)]">
            <div class="flex gap-4 items-start">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-brand-accent)] flex items-center justify-center shrink-0">
                <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="white" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-base text-[var(--color-brand-primary)]">About our endodontic services</h3>
                <p class="mt-1.5 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">
                  Endodontic services at Able Family Dental are provided by our general dentist team. Our dentists are not licensed specialists in endodontics.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- RIGHT: Sidebar -->
        <aside class="space-y-6">

          <!-- Book CTA card -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] rounded-2xl p-6 text-white">
            <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-white">Ready to Book?</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] leading-relaxed">Call us or book your appointment online.</p>
            <a href="/book/" class="mt-4 btn btn-primary w-full block text-center">Book Appointment</a>
            <a href="/refer/" class="mt-2 btn btn-outline w-full block text-center">Refer Patient</a>
            <a href="tel:+14033277202" class="mt-2 block text-center text-sm text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] hover:text-white transition-colors">403.327.7202</a>
          </div>

          <!-- Sibling services card -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-surface-cool)] rounded-2xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border-soft)]">
            <h3 class="font-body text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">Endodontic Services</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              {siblingServices.map(svc => (
                <li>
                  {svc.current ? (
                    <span class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-brand-accent)]">
                      <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-brand-accent)] shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                      {svc.name}
                    </span>
                  ) : (
                    <a href={svc.href} class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] hover:text-[var(--color-brand-accent)] transition-colors">
                      <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-border-soft)] shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                      {svc.name}
                    </a>
                  )}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>

        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       CTA BAND
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] py-16 text-center overflow-hidden relative">
    <svg class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full pointer-events-none" viewBox="0 0 1440 160" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
      <path d="M0 60 C 240 20, 480 100, 720 60 C 960 20, 1200 100, 1440 60 L1440 160 L0 160 Z" fill="rgba(255,255,255,0.03)"/>
    </svg>
    <div class="relative container-wide">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-4xl)] text-white leading-tight">Concerned about a cracked tooth?</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] text-lg max-w-xl mx-auto">Call <a href="tel:+14033277202" class="text-white font-semibold hover:text-[var(--color-brand-accent-soft)] transition-colors">403.327.7202</a> or book an assessment.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/book/" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Book Appointment</a>
        <a href="/refer/" class="btn btn-lg border border-white/30 text-white hover:bg-white/10 transition-colors">Refer Patient</a>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-lg border border-white/30 text-white hover:bg-white/10 transition-colors">Contact Us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
